Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Baking Potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a medium #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium-high heat.

Melt in the @Butter{20%g}. When hot, add half the garlic and stir-fry for
~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and the cold @Water{300%ml}
and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover
with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, cut the @Cauliflower{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any
large ones.

Halfway through roasting, add the cauliflower and @Curry Powder Mix{1} to the
potato baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss everything to evenly coat. Spread out in an even layer and roast on
the top shelf for the remaining time until golden and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While everything cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.
Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @Cashew Nuts{25%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until
lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer to a #bowl{}, then set aside.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{}. Once hot, add the shallot and green beans. Cook until softened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the veg has softened, stir the @Tikka Masala Paste{75%g} and remaining
@Garlic Clove{1}(grated) into the pan.

Cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @Tomato Passata{1} and @Water{100%ml}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir in the roasted veg and three quarters of the
@Creme Fraiche{75%g}. Cook until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon into your
bowls.

Share the veg curry out alongside, then top with a spoonful of the remaining
creme fraiche.

Scatter the toasted cashews over the top to finish. Enjoy!